    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Oath-Broken Draugr are the remnants of hirdmen — warriors who swore oaths to protect their lords and failed. Better-preserved than thralls, they wear the remains of a hirdman's armour and their eyes hold a dull, hateful intelligence. They fight with remembered skill — flanking, retreating from fire, and targeting isolated opponents. When they fall, they whisper one true thing: a fragment of memory from their former life.</p>",
      "director": "<p>The Oath-Broken Draugr is a mid-level brute that fights smart. Use <strong>Tactical Dead</strong> to justify intelligent positioning — it flanks, retreats from fire, and targets isolated PCs. <strong>Oath-Blade</strong> deals solid flat damage (7) with cold ongoing on tier 3. Save <strong>Accusing Howl</strong> (5 Malice) for a key moment — the bane on the target's next power roll can turn a pivotal action. <strong>The Dead Remember</strong> adds narrative weight when it dies — have it whisper a name, a broken promise, or a memory of the world before. Use 2 of these alongside the Wight-Lord to create a dangerous vanguard.</p>",
      "languages": []
    },
